snippet.description:
VIKRANT GUPTA, DAY 3 REPORT: India's rising star Nitish Reddy hit a brilliant hundred and was beautifully complemented by Washington Sundar's rearguard as India reached 358 for 9 before rain forced early stumps on Day 3 of the Boxing Day Test at the Melbourne Cricket Ground. Nitish and Sundar added 127 runs for the eighth wicket to cut India's deficit to 116 after Australia's 474 in Melbourne.
Day 3 was Test cricket at its raw and pulsating best, a reminder of why the Australia-India rivalry stands at the pinnacle of the format. Reddy and Sundar fought back, but Australia remained in a strong position, poised to secure a significant first-innings lead.

snippet.title: Ennu Swantham Punyalan Trailer |  Mahesh Madhu | Arjun Ashokan | Balu Varghese | Anaswara Rajan
snippet.description:
Presenting the Official Trailer Of ‚Äò‚ÄôEnnu Swantham Punyalan, Directed by debutant Mahesh Madhu. Starring Arjun Ashokan, Balu Varghese, and Anaswara Rajan in exciting new roles, the film is written by Samji M Antony. Produced by Ligo John under the banner of Truth Seekers Productions and distributed by Listin Stephan's Magic Frames, the film features music by Sam C.S. and an impressive supporting cast, including Renji Panicker, Baiju, and Althaf.

Mark your calendars‚ÄîEnnu Swantham Punyalan hits theaters on January 10, 2025!

snippet.title: ‡∞∏‡±Ç‡∞™‡∞∞‡±ç ‡∞π‡∞ø‡∞ü‡±ç ‡∞®‡±ç‡∞Ø‡±Ç ‡∞á‡∞Ø‡∞∞‡±ç ‡∞∏‡±ç‡∞™‡±Ü‡∞∑‡∞≤‡±ç ‡∞®‡∞æ‡∞®‡±ç ‡∞µ‡±Ü‡∞ú‡±ç ‡∞§‡∞æ‡∞≤‡∞ø | Exciting New Year Special Non Veg Thali @VismaiFood
snippet.description:
Hello Foodies !! Welcome to Vismai Food !!.

Today we are presenting the new year special exciting non veg thali in Vismai Food's non-vegetarian thali series. This non-vegetarian thali can be prepared easily at home. This non-vegetarian thali includes six amazing recipes: Mutton dum biryani, Gongura Chicken, Carrot Anjeer Semiya Payasam, Mustard Fish, Tawa Chicken Roast, Brinjal Curry. This non-vegetarian recipe is super perfect for this coming happy newyear year party, weekend parties, birthdays, family function and any other events. If you are looking for a amazing non veg meals recipe, this vismai food's special nonveg thali is an excellent choice. Simply follow the steps and procedures outlined in this video to prepare a perfect thali at any time. All of the ingredients are readily available. Take a look at the ingredient list below. Do try this amazing non-veg thali and leave your feedback in the comments section. You can also share the photos on Instagram by tagging Vismai Food.

#happynewyear #nonvegthali #newyearthali #nonvegthaliseries #weekendthalirecipe #gongurachicken #kajupulao #vismaifood #vismaifoodrecipes #vismaifoodthaliseries

Detailed recipes with Ingredients and Method in English & Telugu visit https://www.vismaifood.com

Check out our kitchenware, appliances, utensils, and ingredients by the following link: 

Vismai Food's Amazon Store üõí: https://www.amazon.in/shop/vismaifood

Ingredients:
For Tawa Chicken Roast:
12-15 Dry Chilies
12-15 Garlic pods
1 inch Ginger
1 Star anise
1.5 inch Cinnamon
1/2 tsp Cumin
3-4 Cloves
1 tsp Stone flower
Salt
1/4 tsp Turmeric
3 tbsp Oil for Marination
1 Lemon Juice
750 gms Tandoori cut Chicken
1/4 cup for Roastings

For Mustard Fish:
3 tbsp Soaked Mustard¬†
2 Green Chilies
1/2 inch Ginger
5-6 Garlic Pods (grind to a fine paste)
500 gms Boneless Fish
Salt
1/4 tsp Turmeric
1/2 tbsp Chili Powder
1/2 tsp Black Pepper
2 tbsp Corn flour
1 tbsp Maida
Oil for Deep Frying

For Carrot Anjeer Semiya Payasam:
1/2 litre Milk
3/4 cup Semiya
1/2 cup Carrot gratings
5-6 Anjeer choppings
3 tbsp Ghee
1/2 litre Water
3/4 cup-1 cup Condensed Milk
1/2 tsp Vanilla essence
3 tbsp Cashews
2 tbsp Raisins

For Gongura Chicken:
1/3 cup Oil
7-8 Garlic pods
1/2 tsp Cumin
2 Dry Chilies
2 sprigs Curry leaves
1/2 cup Onion choppings
2 slit green chilies
1 tbsp Ginger garlic paste
1/2 Kilo Chicken
1 Tomato slices
2 tbsp Chili Powder
1/2 tsp Turmeric
1 tsp Coriander powder
1 tsp Roasted Cumin powder
1/2 tsp Garam Masala
Salt
200 gms Gongura
1.1/4 cup Water

For Mutton Dum Biryani:
1/2 kilo MUtton
50 gms Mutton Fat
1/4 cup Oil
1/4 cup Ghee
7-8 Green Cardamoms
8-10 Cloves
3 inch Cinnamon
1 Star anise
2 tbsp Stone flower
3-4 Bay leaves
1 cup malai curd
1.5 tbsp Shahi Jeera
2 Onion slices
3 Green Chilies pieces
2 tbsp Ginger garlic paste
2 Tomato cubes
1 litre Water
Fist full Mint & Coriander
1/2 kilo Rice
1/4 cup Milk
2 Lemon Juice
2.5 tbsp Chili powder
1/2 tbsp Coriander powder
1/2 tbsp Roasted Cumin Powder
1/2 tbsp Garam masala
1/2 tsp Turmeric
Salt
1/4 cup Ghee

For Brinjal Curry:
3 tbsp Peanuts¬†

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.
